            <fr:display-uri>idem-comm-CJ99</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/idem-comm-CJ99/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Retrocompact subsets in spectra">Retrocompact subsets in spectra</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  An open subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/topl-DMH2/" title="Retrocompact subspaces" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/topl-DMH2/" display-uri="topl-DMH2" type="local">retrocompact</fr:link> iff it is compact. 
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>8</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  This is just due to the fact that spectra are also <fr:link href="/topl-GW93/" title="Quasi-separated spaces" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/topl-GW93/" display-uri="topl-GW93" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link>.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>6</fr:month>
              <fr:day>8</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://www.my-great-forest.net/schm-269K/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>schm-269K</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/schm-269K/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Topology of a general scheme">Topology of a general scheme</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  It is well-known that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link>, then as a topological space it is <fr:link href="/topl-FII1/" title="Sober spaces" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/topl-FII1/" display-uri="topl-FII1" type="local">sober</fr:link> and <html:em>locally compact</html:em>. However, it may fail to be <fr:link href="/topl-GW93/" title="Quasi-separated spaces" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/topl-GW93/" display-uri="topl-GW93" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link> or compact.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
